    "Jin et al. (2018) made the connection between dilated convolutions and wavelet analysis, which involves iterative filtering and downsampling steps, and proposed a network structure based on the Cooley-Tukey Fast Fourier Transform (FFT) (Cooley and Tukey, 1965), capable of real-time synthesis.",
    "Similarly sub-band coding through pseudo-mirror quadrature filters (PQMF) was applied to enable greater parallelisation of WaveRNN-based models (Yu et al., 2020).",
